

# Typing Speed Tester
## Description

This is a Typing Speed Tester application built using Python and the `tkinter` library. It allows you to test your typing speed by displaying random words that you need to type within a certain time frame. The application calculates your typing speed in Words Per Minute (WPM) and provides instant feedback on your performance.

## Table of Contents

- [Description](#description)
- [Demo](#demo)
- [Features](#features)
- [Installation](#installation)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [Contributing](#contributing)
- [License](#license)


## Features

- Random word generation for typing practice.
- Instant feedback on your typing speed in WPM.
- User-friendly GUI built using `tkinter`.
- Light red background with white text for a pleasant interface.

## Installation

1. Clone the repository to your local machine:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git
```

2. Ensure you have Python installed (version 3.x recommended).

3. Install the required dependencies:

```bash
# Assuming you are in the project directory
pip install tkinter
```

## Usage

1. Navigate to the project directory.

2. Run the `typing_speed_tester.py` script:

```bash
python wpm_speed.py
```

3. The application window will open, showing a random word for you to type.

4. Type the word in the entry field and press Enter.

5. The application will display your typing speed in WPM and prompt you with the next word.

